('regard-clinical', 'Regard', 'AI-powered clinical decision support that automates diagnoses and notes',
 E'Regard is a clinical decision support platform that uses AI to analyze patient data in real time and suggest diagnoses, generate clinical notes, and surface care gaps directly inside the EHR. Unlike standalone documentation tools, Regard integrates deeply with Epic, Cerner, and Athenahealth to read structured patient data (labs, imaging, vitals, history) and produce diagnostic suggestions ranked by clinical likelihood with citations to source guidelines.\n\nThe platform reduces missed diagnoses by surfacing conditions that match the patient''s data pattern but might be overlooked under time pressure. For hospitalist teams managing complex multi-system patients, Regard typically catches 5-15% additional billable diagnoses per admission by identifying conditions documented elsewhere in the chart but not in the clinician''s note. The financial ROI is straightforward to calculate from incremental DRG capture.\n\nRegard targets hospital systems and large physician groups rather than solo practices. Implementation requires Epic or Cerner access, clinical leadership buy-in, and 60-90 days of training data curation. Pricing is custom and typically structured per encounter or per facility. Major academic medical centers including Stanford and Cedars-Sinai have published peer-reviewed validation of the platform.',
 'https://withregard.com', 'https://withregard.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.6, 280, false, true, false,
 ARRAY['healthcare', 'ai-assistants', 'analytics'],
 ARRAY['Real-time diagnostic suggestions ranked by clinical likelihood with citations', 'Native integration with Epic, Cerner, Athenahealth for structured data access', 'Measurable DRG capture lift translates to direct hospital revenue', 'Peer-reviewed validation at major academic medical centers'],
 ARRAY['Custom enterprise pricing not transparent until sales call', 'Implementation requires Epic or Cerner access and clinical leadership buy-in', 'Less applicable to solo practices or small clinics', 'Training data curation phase delays time-to-value 60-90 days'],
 ARRAY['Hospital diagnostic decision support and DRG capture optimization', 'Clinical note generation for hospitalist and inpatient workflows', 'Care gap identification for value-based care contracts'],
 NOW()),

('viz-ai', 'Viz.ai', 'AI medical imaging platform for stroke, cardiac, and emergency care',
 E'Viz.ai is the leading AI medical imaging platform for time-critical conditions like stroke, pulmonary embolism, and cardiac events. The platform analyzes CT, MRI, and other imaging studies the moment they are acquired and notifies the right specialist immediately if AI detects a high-risk finding. For stroke care specifically, Viz.ai has been shown to reduce time-to-treatment by 40+ minutes - which directly improves patient outcomes given the time-dependent nature of stroke recovery.\n\nThe platform sits between the imaging system and the specialist''s phone or workstation. When a patient arrives at an emergency department with stroke symptoms, the CT imaging is automatically analyzed by Viz.ai algorithms within minutes. If a large vessel occlusion is detected, the neurointerventional team is paged simultaneously with image access pushed to their mobile device, eliminating the traditional radiologist-to-specialist handoff delay.\n\nViz.ai partners with major stroke centers, cardiac care networks, and integrated delivery systems. The FDA has cleared multiple Viz.ai algorithms for clinical use, and the platform is reimbursable under specific Medicare codes for stroke care coordination. Pricing is per-facility or per-network and typically negotiated as part of broader care coordination contracts.',
 'https://viz.ai', 'https://viz.ai',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.7, 1100, false, true, false,
 ARRAY['healthcare', 'ai-assistants', 'image-ai'],
 ARRAY['FDA-cleared algorithms for stroke, PE, and cardiac event detection', 'Reduces time-to-treatment by 40+ minutes for stroke patients in deployments', 'Mobile-first specialist notification eliminates radiologist handoff delay', 'Reimbursable under specific Medicare codes for stroke care'],
 ARRAY['Hospital-only deployment model; not applicable to outpatient settings', 'Requires integration with PACS imaging infrastructure', 'Custom pricing varies significantly by facility size and condition coverage', 'Most beneficial for facilities with sufficient stroke or cardiac volume'],
 ARRAY['Stroke detection and rapid neurointerventional team notification', 'Pulmonary embolism triage from CT pulmonary angiography', 'Cardiac event detection and care team coordination'],
 NOW()),

('paige-ai', 'Paige', 'AI-powered pathology platform for cancer detection and diagnosis',
 E'Paige is the leading AI platform for pathology, focused on cancer detection and diagnosis from digitized tissue slide images. The platform analyzes whole-slide images using deep learning models trained on millions of annotated cases to detect cancer with sensitivity comparable to expert pathologists. For prostate cancer specifically, Paige Prostate became the first FDA-authorized AI pathology product in the United States.\n\nThe AI workflow sits inside the pathologist''s digital reading environment. When a slide is imaged, Paige automatically pre-analyzes it for high-risk regions, providing a heatmap showing tumor likelihood and a quantitative grade assessment. Pathologists review the AI findings alongside the slide, accepting or modifying as appropriate. This human-in-the-loop approach maintains physician judgment while reducing missed diagnoses and accelerating turnaround time.\n\nPaige partners with pathology labs, cancer centers, and academic medical institutions. Pricing is per-slide or per-case, typically negotiated as part of digital pathology infrastructure deployments. The platform requires whole-slide imaging scanners and digital pathology software (Sectra, Philips IntelliSite, or similar) as the imaging foundation.',
 'https://paige.ai', 'https://paige.ai',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.5, 340, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['healthcare', 'image-ai', 'analytics'],
 ARRAY['First FDA-authorized AI pathology product in the United States (Paige Prostate)', 'Sensitivity comparable to expert pathologists in published clinical studies', 'Heatmap visualization keeps pathologist in the diagnostic loop', 'Reduces turnaround time and missed diagnoses in high-volume pathology labs'],
 ARRAY['Requires whole-slide imaging infrastructure as foundation', 'Per-slide pricing scales with case volume and may not fit small labs', 'Limited cancer types currently covered; expanding to additional indications', 'Requires lab digital pathology workflow already in place'],
