('atropos-health', 'Atropos Health', 'On-demand real-world evidence for clinical decision-making',
 E'Atropos Health generates on-demand real-world evidence for clinicians and life sciences researchers by analyzing de-identified patient data from health systems and academic medical centers. The platform answers specific clinical questions ("for patients like mine with these conditions, what was the outcome of treatment X versus treatment Y?") by running rapid retrospective cohort studies on real patient populations.\n\nThe killer use case is the consult-style query. A clinician facing a complex patient where guidelines are ambiguous can submit a structured question to Atropos and receive a peer-reviewed-quality cohort analysis within hours, not the weeks or months a traditional retrospective study would take. The platform powers similar workflows for pharma medical affairs teams answering payer questions, formulary committees evaluating new drugs, and policy researchers studying treatment patterns.\n\nAtropos partners with health systems for the underlying data and offers different products for clinicians, researchers, and pharma. Pricing is custom and structured around query volume or institutional licenses. The company spun out of Stanford research and maintains close ties with academic medical centers for data access and methodology validation.',
 'https://atroposhealth.com', 'https://atroposhealth.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.6, 180, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['healthcare', 'analytics', 'research'],
 ARRAY['On-demand cohort studies in hours rather than weeks or months', 'De-identified data from health systems plus academic centers for representative populations', 'Peer-reviewed-quality methodology with biostatistician oversight', 'Multiple products: clinician consult, pharma medical affairs, policy research'],
 ARRAY['Custom enterprise pricing not transparent until sales call', 'Limited utility for queries outside the platform''s data coverage', 'Requires structured question formulation - not natural language conversational AI', 'Newer brand with smaller community than traditional clinical research vendors'],
