('heidi-health', 'Heidi Health', 'AI medical scribe that listens to consultations and writes notes automatically',
 E'Heidi Health is an AI medical scribe that listens to clinician-patient conversations during consultations and produces structured clinical notes in real time. The platform handles the dictation, summarization, ICD coding suggestion, and EHR formatting that consume 30-40% of a clinician''s day, freeing them to focus on patient interaction rather than documentation.\n\nWhat differentiates Heidi from earlier ambient documentation tools is the structured note quality and EHR integration. The notes follow SOAP format, include differential diagnoses with reasoning, and integrate with Epic, Cerner, Practice Fusion, and other major EHRs. Clinicians review and sign off on the AI-generated notes rather than dictating from scratch, which typically reduces documentation time by 60-70%.\n\nHeidi targets primary care physicians, specialists, and outpatient clinics. The platform supports group practice deployments with practice manager oversight, custom note templates per clinician, and audit trails for compliance. Pricing is per-clinician per-month, with significant volume discounts for group practice deployments. The company is based in Australia but serves clinicians globally.',
 'https://heidihealth.com.au', 'https://heidihealth.com.au',
 'freemium', true, 99, 4.7, 620, false, true, false,
 ARRAY['healthcare', 'ai-assistants', 'productivity'],
 ARRAY['Free tier available for individual clinicians to test the workflow', 'Structured SOAP notes with differential diagnosis reasoning included', 'Integration with Epic, Cerner, Practice Fusion, and major EHRs', 'Reduces documentation time by 60-70% in deployment studies'],
 ARRAY['Quality varies for accents and non-English consultations', 'Per-clinician pricing scales linearly with practice size', 'Best results require clinicians to follow structured consultation patterns', 'EHR integration depth varies by platform; some require manual paste workflow'],
 ARRAY['Outpatient consultation documentation for primary care and specialists', 'Group practice deployment with practice manager oversight', 'Telehealth visit documentation with automatic structured note generation'],
