('hippocratic-ai', 'Hippocratic AI', 'Safety-focused LLM and AI agents for non-diagnostic patient interactions',
 E'Hippocratic AI is a healthcare-specific large language model and AI agent platform built specifically for non-diagnostic patient interactions. The company''s thesis is that LLMs trained on general internet data are unsafe for healthcare deployment - so they built a model trained from the ground up on medical literature, clinical guidelines, and validated patient-interaction transcripts. The platform powers AI agents for patient navigation, post-discharge follow-up, medication adherence, chronic care management, and pre-visit screening.\n\nThe safety thesis is the differentiator. Hippocratic deliberately limits the model from making diagnostic recommendations, prescribing decisions, or other interactions where AI hallucination could cause patient harm. Instead, the AI agents handle scripted but personalized conversations - reminding patients about medications, screening for symptoms before appointments, coordinating care between providers, and escalating to humans when clinical judgment is needed.\n\nHippocratic AI partners with health systems and care management organizations for deployment. The agents typically replace high-volume call center work while extending care reach into patient populations that traditional staffing cannot cover. Pricing is custom and structured around agent hours or covered patients. Major health system pilots have published outcomes showing comparable patient satisfaction to human navigators at significantly lower cost per interaction.',
 'https://hippocraticai.com', 'https://hippocraticai.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.4, 220, false, true, false,
 ARRAY['healthcare', 'ai-assistants', 'voice-audio'],
 ARRAY['Healthcare-specific LLM trained on medical literature and validated transcripts', 'Safety-first design avoids diagnostic and prescribing decisions', 'Voice-capable agents handle non-diagnostic care navigation at scale', 'Cost-effective coverage for chronic care management and post-discharge follow-up'],
 ARRAY['Custom enterprise pricing not transparent until sales call', 'Deliberately limited scope - not applicable to diagnostic decision support', 'Requires health system partnership for deployment context', 'Newer company with limited deployment history compared to established care management vendors'],
 ARRAY['Post-discharge follow-up and medication adherence coordination', 'Pre-visit symptom screening and patient navigation', 'Chronic care management voice agent deployment for high-volume populations'],
 NOW()),

('deepscribe', 'DeepScribe', 'Ambient AI medical scribe with deep EHR integration',
 E'DeepScribe is an ambient AI medical scribe that listens to clinician-patient conversations and writes structured clinical notes inside the clinician''s existing EHR. The differentiator versus competitors like Heidi or Freed is the depth of EHR integration: DeepScribe writes directly into Epic, Cerner, Athenahealth, and others rather than generating notes for paste, eliminating the manual transcription step entirely.\n\nThe platform supports multiple specialties with specialty-specific note templates, ICD coding suggestions, and integration with billing workflows. Clinicians focus on the patient conversation while DeepScribe handles documentation in the background. Notes are generated in real time during the encounter, with the clinician reviewing and signing off afterward. Studies show 70-80% reduction in documentation time and improved patient face-time during encounters.\n\nDeepScribe targets group practices, specialty clinics, and health system deployments. The platform is HIPAA-compliant with BAA available, SOC 2 Type II certified, and supports group billing for enterprise deployments. Pricing is per-clinician per-month with custom enterprise discounts for large health systems. Implementation requires EHR access and 1-2 weeks of clinician onboarding for note style calibration.',
